Are deliveries more on-time in specific states?
------To determine if deliveries are more on-time in specific states, we need to analyze the on_time_flag column grouped by the location_state column in the datawerhouse1.bronze.delivery_events table. By calculating the percentage of on-time deliveries for each state, we can identify which states have better on-time performance. The following SQL query will provide this analysis:
SELECT 
    `location_state`, 
    AVG(CASE WHEN `on_time_flag` THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100 AS on_time_percentage
FROM 
    `datawerhouse1`.`bronze`.`delivery_events`
GROUP BY 
    `location_state`
ORDER BY 
    on_time_percentage DESC
  
---This query calculates the average of the on_time_flag (considering it as 1 for TRUE and 0 for FALSE) for each state, and multiplies it by 100 to get the percentage of deliveries that are on time. It then orders the results by this percentage in descending order, highlighting the states with the highest on-time delivery performance.

